    Generated pattern matcher API of the org.eclipse.viatra.integration.uml.derivedfeatures.stateIsComposite pattern, providing pattern-specific query methods.

    Use the pattern matcher on a given model via on(ViatraQueryEngine), e.g. in conjunction with ViatraQueryEngine#on(Notifier).

    Matches of the pattern will be represented as StateIsCompositeMatch.

    Original source: 

     (region->notEmpty())
 
 @Surrogate(feature = "isComposite")
 @QueryExplorer(checked = false)
 pattern stateIsComposite(
     self : State, isComposite
 ) {
     find stateIsComposite_0(self, _region);
     isComposite == true;
 } or {
     neg find stateIsComposite_0(self, _region);
     isComposite == false;
 }
